'''Marondera District''' is a [[Districts of Zimbabwe|district]] of [[Mashonaland East Province]], [[Zimbabwe]], in southern Africa.<ref>{{GEOnet2|32FA881EA1E63774E0440003BA962ED3|Marondera District (Approved)}}, [[National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency|United States National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency]]</ref><ref>{{Cite map|publisher=Surveyor General, Zimbabwe|title=Zimbabwe. Chegutu. Sheet SE-36-09|scale=1:250,0000|edition=1990|url=http://eusoils.jrc.it/esdb_archive/EuDASM/africa/images/maps/download/afr_zw3002_16to.jpg|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070318092842/http://eusoils.jrc.it/esdb_archive/EuDASM/africa/images/maps/download/afr_zw3002_16to.jpg|archivedate=18 March 2007|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite map|publisher=Surveyor General, Zimbabwe|title=Zimbabwe. Mutare. Sheet SE-36-10|scale=1:250,0000|edition=1974|url=http://eusoils.jrc.it/esdb_archive/EuDASM/africa/images/maps/download/afr_zw3002_17to.jpg|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070318092903/http://eusoils.jrc.it/esdb_archive/EuDASM/africa/images/maps/download/afr_zw3002_17to.jpg|archivedate=18 March 2007|deadurl=yes}}</ref> It is located in the eastern part of Zimbabwe, and covers an unknown area. The district capital is the town of [[Marondera]], which is also the provincial capital.

==Geography==
Marondera District is divided into four parliamentary constituencies: Marondera East constituency, Marondera West constituency, Marondera Central constituency, and a small northern portion of Wezda North constituency (most of which is in [[Wedza District]]). Marondera Central comprises only Marondera Town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Marondera Central constituency|year=2011|publisher=Research Department, Parliament of Zimbabwe|url=http://www.parlzim.gov.zw/attachments/article/130/Marondera%20Central.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140423222223/http://www.parlzim.gov.zw/attachments/article/130/Marondera%20Central.pdf|archivedate=23 April 2014|deadurl=no}}</ref> Marondera West constituency comprises the Chihota communal area and includes the business centres at Mahusekwa, Chiwanzamarara and Manyaira.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Marondera West constituency|publisher=Research Department, Parliament of Zimbabwe|year=2011|url=http://www.parlzim.gov.zw/attachments/article/130/Marondera%20West.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140423222201/http://www.parlzim.gov.zw/attachments/article/130/Marondera%20West.pdf|archivedate=23 April 2014|deadurl=no}}</ref> Marondera East constituency comprises the Svosve communal lands, and the Rhodesclarke, 
Chitangazuva, Waddilove, Musi and Mukute, Surrey and Dambi Estates areas.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Marondera East constituency|publisher=Research Department, Parliament of Zimbabwe|year=2011|url=http://www.parlzim.gov.zw/attachments/article/130/Marondera%20East.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140423223138/http://www.parlzim.gov.zw/attachments/article/130/Marondera%20East.pdf|archivedate=23 April 2014|deadurl=no}}</ref>

Rivers in the district include the [[Save River (Africa)|Save]], the Mtoromanzi, and the Nyakambiri.

